properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 8 at 8:14AM MST until February 8 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...TRAVEL IMPACTS WILL CONTINUE ALONG AND WEST OF THE LARAMIE RANGE
THROUGH THIS AFTERNOON...

* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow. Additional snow accumulations of
up to one inch. Winds gusting as high as 60 mph.

* WHERE...North Snowy Range Foothills including Arlington and Elk
Mountain.

* WHEN...Until 5 PM MST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Widespread blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON... ...BLIZZARD WARNING IS CANCELLED
